        public void setNetworkMask(@NonNull
                           java.lang.String netmask)
        This option is very important: in shared network environment and yarn (like on EC2 etc), please set this to the network, which will be available on all boxes. I.e. 10.1.1.0/24 or 192.168.0.0/16
        Parameters:
        netmask - netmask to be used for IP address selection
